history.content: In the first week, the beanstalk was 3 inches tall. In the second week, it doubled in size so it was 2*3 = 6 inches. After the third week, it was reported to be 10 inches tall. The growth in the third week can be found by subtracting the height after the second week from the height after the third week. Thus, the third week growth is 10 - 6 = 4 inches.
